In the Matter of Fred T. Santucci, Appellant, v. James M. Power et al., Constituting the Board of Elections of the City of New York, and Eugene J. McMahon, Respondents. Argued May 27, 1964; decided May 27, 1964. *766John Santucci, Hyman J. Greenberg and Lawrence Peirez, for appellant. Lewis Abrahams and Sidney A. Littman for Eugene J. McMahon, respondent.

No appearance for remaining respondents.

*767Order affirmed, without costs; no opinion.

Concur: Chief Judge Desmond and Judges Dye, Fold, Van Voorhis, Burke, Scileppi and Hamm*.

Designated pursuant to section 2 of article VI of the State Constitution in the temporary absence of Judge Bergan.
